'They came down, investigated, found a substance, they buried it, and exploded it,' he said.

'They didn't want to take it away on precaution; they didn't know what it was so they just buried it. It was in a bag, they didn't uncover the bag, they just took [it] as it was, and buried it. 

It has been reported that the bomb may have been linked to the 1988 prisoner riots, where officers were overthrown and the prison was set on fire.

