Fremantle Prison operated as a maximum for almost 140 years before it was decommissioned in 1991. 

Daily tours operate out of the prison and it is listed as as one of the top tourist attractions in Perth. 

Since opening to the public in 1992, the prison has seen over three million visitors walk through the doors.   

 

